1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new architecture for human pose estimation in monocular images using deep Convolutional Networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses joint training of two different model paradigms to improve performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new hybrid architecture that can exploit structural domain constraints. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with human pose estimation in images. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses deep Convolutional Networks for human pose estimation.
